SIMPLE: wretchedness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wretchedness
<hw>Wretch"ed*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or
state of being wretched; utter misery.</def> <rj><au>Sir W.
Raleigh.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A wretched object; anything despicably.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Eat worms and such <qex>wretchedness</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wretchful</ent>⟦br⟧
